articles.title: The full 'Beaver Moon' rises next to bright Jupiter this weekend. Here's how to watch. - Livescience.com
articles.description: The full 'Beaver Moon' will be best viewed as it rises in the east at dusk on Monday, Nov. 27, though it will appear full on Sunday and Tuesday as well.
articles.content:
On Monday, Nov. 27, look east in the evening to see the full "Beaver Moon" rise into the sky.
November's full moon occurs as Earth gets between the sun and moon. It's consequently 100% illuminated —… [+1612 chars]
